snippet.title: Five Nights at Freddy's 2 | Official Trailer 2
snippet.description:
A new set of rules. A new level of fear. Five Nights at Freddy‚Äôs 2 only in theaters December 5. Get tickets now.

---

In 2023, Blumhouse‚Äôs box-office horror phenomenon Five Nights at Freddy‚Äôs, based on the blockbuster game series by Scott Cawthon, became the highest-grossing horror film of the year. Now, a shocking new chapter of animatronic terror begins. 
 
One year has passed since the supernatural nightmare at Freddy Fazbear‚Äôs Pizza. The stories about what transpired there have been twisted into a campy local legend, inspiring the town‚Äôs first ever Fazfest. 
 
Former security guard Mike (Josh Hutcherson) and police officer Vanessa (Elizabeth Lail) have kept the truth from Mike‚Äôs 11-year-old sister, Abby (Piper Rubio), concerning the fate of her animatronic friends. 
 
But when Abby sneaks out to reconnect with Freddy, Bonnie, Chica, and Foxy, it will set into motion a terrifying series of events, revealing dark secrets about the true origin of Freddy‚Äôs, and unleashing a long-forgotten horror hidden away for decades.
 
The cast of Five Nights at Freddy‚Äôs 2 includes returning co-stars Theodus Crane as Jeremiah and the legendary Matthew Lillard as William Afton. The film features new characters played by Freddy Carter (Shadow and Bone, Pennyworth), Wayne Knight (Jurassic Park, Seinfeld), Mckenna Grace (Ghostbusters franchise, Annabelle Comes Home) and horror icon Skeet Ulrich (Scream, Riverdale). 
 
Five Nights at Freddy‚Äôs 2 is directed by acclaimed returning filmmaker Emma Tammi and is written by game series creator Scott Cawthon.
 
The film is produced by Blumhouse founder and CEO Jason Blum and Scott Cawthon, who together produced the first film. The executive producers are director Emma Tammi, Beatriz Sequeira, Christopher Warner, Russell Binder and Marc Mostman. 
 
The first Freddy‚Äôs film opened to a record-shattering $80 million in October 2023 and went on to earn almost $300 million worldwide.

Covering The Mummy 4 Teaser Announcement. Brendan Fraser & Rachel Weisz Return for a legacy sequel to The Mummy Returns (The Mummy 2). They are ignoring the events of The Mummy 3 Tomb of the Dragon Emperor. Explaining why Rachel Weisz left the franchise earlier, and why they're pretending like The Mummy 3 never happened. What this means for the plot of The Mummy 4. Other returning original legacy characters.

This is meant to be similar to Marvel bringing back Hugh Jackman as Wolverine during  Deadpool and Wolverine, Avengers Doomsday & Avengers Secret Wars. And explaining Universal's brief attempt to turn The Mummy Movies into a Marvel franchise with The Dark Universe Teaser with the Tom Cruise Mummy Movie 2017. And why that failed. 

I'll do more videos for The Mummy 4 once they release a trailer or footage. We'll get more news and announcements next year.

There's lots of big stuff coming before the end of the year, Marvel Avengers Doomsday Trailer, Spider-Man Brand New Day Trailer, Lanterns Trailer for Green Lantern, Superman 2 Man of Tomorrow, Supergirl Trailer, and lots more!

My full IT Welcome to Derry Episode 3 video will post sunday too!

snippet.title: Marvel Studios' Wonder Man - Official 'Stream On January 27' Trailer (2026) Yahya Abdul-Mateen II
snippet.description:
Don't miss the 'Stream On January 27' Trailer for Wonder Man, the next action-adventure superhero installment in the MCU distributed by Marvel Studios. 

Hollywood actor Simon Williams is thrust into the world of superheroes as he gets powers of his own, and becomes the new superhero Wonder Man.

Wonder Man stars Yahya Abdul-Mateen II, Ben Kingsley, Demetrius Grosse, Lauren Glazier, Byron Bowers, and more. The series was created by Destin Daniel Cretton.

Wonder Man premieres January 27 at 6 PM PT only on Disney+
